+++Mantle Mist Cinder Rubble Aqua Truttle Cyndro::

The eletors split up into seperate bots again when the battle ended. They 
watches the Decepticons leave and smiled.

"That was pretty good." Mantle said while they made their way to a group of 
Maximals. They were about to greet them when Iron Raptor called everyone to 
attention, and they followed everyone else's example and got into line.


Truttle walked to Cledar and looked at all the robots around him. He then 
spun around and saluted along with Cledar and the rest of his group.


Cyndro scanned all the Decepticons while they retreated and saved them all 
in a file. He knew what tactics they used now and the next battle against 
them would be easier. His nanobots were still working on adapting the 
Cybertronian Fire's shield generators completely to his own, but work was 
going well. A large plate of metal slid apart on top of the center of 
Maximal City and two sets of solar panels emerged. One of the sets was the 
Element's and the other one was the Cybertronian Fire's. The panels quickly 
began powering the ship back up, and the shields almost instantly rose to 
one hundred percent.

Cyndro heard Iron Raptor call to him but she was gone before he could 
answer. He continued his work on the city but kept an eye out for what was 
going on outside with the Maximals while his nano probes began tyding up the 
land and removed scrap and traces of battle from it.
